.SH NAME
circleci-migrate-secrets-merge - Merge multiple secret bundles into one.


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcircleci-migrate secrets merge -o  \&... [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
merge combines several secret bundles (for example, the per-context
bundles produced by separate extraction jobs) into a single bundle.

.PP
When --encrypt is set the merged bundle is written as an age-encrypted file
(\&.age) instead of plaintext. Provide the recipient's public key via
--recipient (inline) or --recipient-file (path to a .pub or age recipients
file). The corresponding private key is required to decrypt with
\&'secrets decrypt'.

.PP
Example:
  circleci-migrate secrets merge -o secrets.json artifacts/\fI/secrets.json
  circleci-migrate secrets merge --encrypt --recipient-file ~/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub \\
    -o secrets.json artifacts/\fP/secrets.json


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--encrypt\fP[=false]
	Encrypt the output bundle with age (writes \&.age; requires --recipient or --recipient-file)

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for merge

.PP
\fB-o\fP, \fB--output\fP="secrets.json"
	Path to write the merged bundle

.PP
\fB--recipient\fP=""
	age or SSH public key recipient string (ssh-ed25519/ssh-rsa/age1...)

.PP
\fB--recipient-file\fP=""
	Path to an SSH public key (.pub) or age recipients file


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--debug\fP[=false]
	Enable debug logging

.PP
\fB--dest-token\fP=""
	API token for the destination org (env: CIRCLECI_DEST_TOKEN)

.PP
\fB--host\fP="https://circleci.com"
	CircleCI host URL (env: CIRCLECI_HOST)

.PP
\fB--source-token\fP=""
	API token for the source org (env: CIRCLECI_SOURCE_TOKEN)

.PP
\fB--token\fP=""
	Personal API token — fallback for both orgs (env: CIRCLECI_CLI_TOKEN)


